## Code Style

### Naming Conventions

```
Components: PascalCase (UserProfile.tsx)
Functions: camelCase (getUserData)
Variables: camelCase (userName)
Constants: UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (MAX_RETRY_COUNT)
Files: kebab-case (user-profile.tsx)
Directories: kebab-case (user-profile/)
```

### Code Organization

```
src/
├── components/     # Reusable components
├── pages/          # Page components
├── hooks/          # Custom Hooks
├── utils/          # Utility functions
├── services/       # API services
├── types/          # Type definitions
└── constants/      # Constant definitions
```

---

## Coding Standards

### TypeScript

- Use strict mode
- Avoid using any, use unknown instead
- Prefer interface for object type definitions
- Use type inference, reduce explicit type annotations

### React

- Use functional components
- Use Hooks for state management
- Component splitting principle: single responsibility
- Props use TypeScript interface definitions

### Error Handling

- Wrap async operations with try-catch
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors
- User-friendly error prompts

---

## Prohibited Items

- ❌ Do not use any type
- ❌ Do not use await in loops
- ❌ Do not directly modify props
- ❌ Do not define functions in render functions
- ❌ Do not use inline styles (unless necessary)
- ❌ Do not commit console.log
- ❌ Do not hardcode sensitive information

---

## Comment Standards

### Language
- Code comments use [Chinese/English]
- Documentation uses [Chinese/English]

### Format

```typescript
/**
 * Function description
 * @param paramName - Parameter description
 * @returns Return value description
 */
function functionName(paramName: Type): ReturnType {
  // Single line comment
  
  /*
   * Multi-line comment
   * Second line
   */
}
```

---

## Git Standards

### Commit Message Format

```
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

<body>

<footer>
```

### Type Categories

- feat: New feature
- fix: Bug fix
- docs: Documentation update
- style: Code format
- refactor: Refactoring
- test: Testing
- chore: Build/tools

---

## Test Standards

### Test File Naming

```
Component tests: ComponentName.test.tsx
Utility tests: utilName.test.ts
Integration tests: feature.integration.test.ts
E2E tests: feature.e2e.test.ts
```

### Test Coverage

- Statement coverage target: > 80%
- Branch coverage target: > 75%
- Core business logic must be tested

---

## Performance Standards

### Frontend

- Image lazy loading
- Component lazy loading
- Debounce/Throttle
- Virtual lists (large data sets)

### Backend

- Database query optimization
- Caching strategy
- Paginated queries
- Connection pool management

---

## Security Standards

- Input validation
- XSS protection
- CSRF protection
- SQL injection protection
- Sensitive data encryption
- HTTPS enforcement

